<subSubSection pageId="10" pageNumber="51" type="nomenclature">
<paragraph blockId="10.[151,1437,375,626]" box="[151,529,375,401]" pageId="10" pageNumber="51">
<heading bold="true" box="[151,529,375,401]" fontSize="11" level="1" pageId="10" pageNumber="51" reason="1">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[151,529,375,401]" pageId="10" pageNumber="51">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[151,394,375,401]" italics="true" pageId="10" pageNumber="51">
“ 
<taxonomicName box="[165,255,375,401]" class="Insecta" family="Tettigoniidae" genus="Eriolus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Orthoptera" pageId="10" pageNumber="51" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">Eriolus</taxonomicName>
” 
<taxonomicName authority="Piza, 1979" authorityName="Piza" authorityYear="1979" box="[277,394,375,401]" class="Insecta" family="Tettigoniidae" genus="Eriolus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Orthoptera" pageId="10" pageNumber="51" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="paruensis">paruensis</taxonomicName>
</emphasis>
Piza, 
<number box="[470,529,375,401]" pageId="10" pageNumber="51" value="1979.0">1979</number>
</emphasis>
</heading>
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="10.[151,1437,375,626]" pageId="10" pageNumber="51">
This species is misplaced in 
<taxonomicName box="[552,638,413,438]" class="Insecta" family="Tettigoniidae" genus="Eriolus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Orthoptera" pageId="10" pageNumber="51" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[552,638,413,438]" italics="true" pageId="10" pageNumber="51">Eriolus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
. All known females of this genus have much shorter and curved ovipostors. 
<taxonomicName box="[291,440,450,475]" class="Insecta" family="Tettigoniidae" genus="Eriolus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Orthoptera" pageId="10" pageNumber="51" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="parunesis">
<emphasis box="[291,440,450,475]" italics="true" pageId="10" pageNumber="51">E. parunesis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
has a straight and much longer ovipositor. Due to the dark coloration of the dorsal area of the pronotum it resembles 
<taxonomicName box="[587,671,488,513]" class="Insecta" family="Tettigoniidae" genus="Subria" kingdom="Animalia" order="Orthoptera" pageId="10" pageNumber="51" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[587,671,488,513]" italics="true" pageId="10" pageNumber="51">Subria</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, as well as 
<taxonomicName box="[821,990,488,513]" class="Insecta" family="Tettigoniidae" genus="Eschatoceras" kingdom="Animalia" order="Orthoptera" pageId="10" pageNumber="51" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[821,990,488,513]" italics="true" pageId="10" pageNumber="51">Eschatoceras</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
. But it does not comply with other characters of those genera, in particular not with the respective 
<typeStatus box="[889,939,525,551]" pageId="10" pageNumber="51">type</typeStatus>
species, although 
<taxonomicName box="[1155,1311,525,550]" class="Insecta" family="Tettigoniidae" genus="Subria" kingdom="Animalia" order="Orthoptera" pageId="10" pageNumber="51" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="amazonica">
<emphasis box="[1155,1311,525,550]" italics="true" pageId="10" pageNumber="51">S. amazonica</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
has a long and straight ovipositor. Even though 
<taxonomicName box="[597,747,562,587]" class="Insecta" family="Tettigoniidae" genus="Eriolus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Orthoptera" pageId="10" pageNumber="51" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="paruensis">
<emphasis box="[597,747,562,587]" italics="true" pageId="10" pageNumber="51">E. paruensis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is not an 
<taxonomicName box="[867,955,562,587]" class="Insecta" family="Tettigoniidae" genus="Eriolus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Orthoptera" pageId="10" pageNumber="51" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[867,955,562,587]" italics="true" pageId="10" pageNumber="51">Eriolus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, we could not find an appropriate place where it belongs, and for now leave it in that genus.
</paragraph>
